This article predates the project, and should be considered non-canon.  &ldquo;The puffin flies here so early (over the years). The further inland we go, the farther they chase us.&rdquo;
That&rsquo;s the sentiment of the phrase, but in Vekllei &lsquo;The puffin flies here&rsquo; is supplemented with the opening of a saying, &lsquo;all birds flee the sea in Winter,&rsquo; and so there is a reference here that is otherwise lost in translation.
